{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-0121"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Vineyard Operations Coordination"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "0121"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :agriculture/grape-growing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:food-security :rural-employment :agricultural-sustainability]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :vineyard-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:telemetry :optimization :dmn :bpmn]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "VineyardOpsAdvisor ⊣ Vineyard Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph (langgraph.graph, vineyardops.operation/build), append-only
 audit ledger (vineyardops.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore).
 Fixes a severe prior gap, worse than the usual deferred-stub pattern:
 `deps.edn` declared the real `io.github.kotoba-lang/langgraph`
 dependency ONLY under the unused `:dev :override-deps` alias (main
 `:deps` was `{}`), so a plain `clojure -M:test`/`clojure -M:run` never
 had `langgraph.graph` on the classpath at all; `operation.cljc`'s OWN
 docstring admitted \"langgraph-clj StateGraph integration is deferred.
 This stub version...\" -- `build` returned a hand-rolled closure over
 `run-operation` with ZERO `state-graph`/`add-node`/`interrupt-before`
 calls anywhere; and `store.cljc` had NO `ledger`/`append-ledger!`
 function AT ALL -- not dead code, the concept was entirely absent from
 `src/`, despite this file's own `:required-technologies [...
 :audit-ledger]` implying one should exist. `blueprint.edn` nonetheless
 claimed `:itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented`, which was false
 given all of the above.
 Now: the real dependency lives in the main `:deps` map; a genuinely
 compiled StateGraph (`:intake -> :advise -> :govern -> :decide -+->
 :commit / :request-approval -> :commit / :hold`) with
 `interrupt-before #{:request-approval}` + in-memory checkpointer for
 real human-in-the-loop resume; and a real `vineyardops.store/ledger` +
 `append-ledger!` genuinely wired into the `:commit`/`:hold` graph
 nodes, not test-only. `vineyardops.advisor`'s proposal builder and
 `vineyardops.governor`'s hard/escalate checks (vineyard/block
 registration, closed op-allowlist, effect-must-be-:propose,
 field-equipment/spray-application permanent block, non-positive
 vineyard-record quantity, category cost threshold, always-escalating
 crop-health-concern) and `vineyardops.phase`'s 0->3 rollout gate are
 reused UNCHANGED -- this fix only wires the existing vineyard
 operations-coordination domain policy into a real compiled graph and a
 real ledger, it does not redesign it.
 Proven end-to-end by `test/vineyardops/operation_test.cljc` (ledger
 stays empty until a real commit, hold-for-unregistered-vineyard/
 non-positive-quantity/blocked-field-equipment/blocked-spray-application
 even at phase-3, phase-0-sandbox escalates a clean proposal,
 escalate-then-approve and escalate-then-reject for the
 always-escalating crop-health-concern flag, high-cost supply-order
 escalation, never-auto-commit for crop-health-concern at every phase)
 through the REAL compiled graph, plus a `clojure -M:dev:run` demo
 runner producing real ledger entries for every scenario. All
 pre-existing advisor/governor/facts/phase/registry/store tests are
 unchanged and still passing. CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`,
 sibling-checkout pattern for `:local/root` deps) was missing entirely
 and is added in this fix."}
